The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 January is 33,598 (3,888.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 January, there were 3,929 new confirmed cases (454.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 January, there were 4,986 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (1,057 fewer cases).
